What is React.StrictMode?
<React.StrictMode> is a wrapper component provided by React. You use it to wrap part or all of your React app to:

Highlight potential issues

Warn about deprecated APIs

Enforce best practices

It runs additional checks to help you catch bugs before they cause problems in production.

What it does?

1. Double Invokes Certain Lifecycle Methods (in dev only)
2. Warns About Deprecated Methods
3. Warns About Unsafe Side Effects
4. Checks for Legacy Context API

